messages.content: ComfyUI-MotionThiefExperiment is an experimental node pack for ComfyUI that tests using reference videos for their motion.
Is ComfyUI-MotionThiefExperiment compatible with many things?
No, ComfyUI-MotionThiefExperiment is not compatible with a lot of things as it is a hacky implementation for experiments only.
Where can I find example workflows for ComfyUI-MotionThiefExperiment?
You can find example workflows for ComfyUI-MotionThiefExperiment in the 'example_workflows' folder.
What type of settings does the example workflow in ComfyUI-MotionThiefExperiment use?
The example workflow in ComfyUI-MotionThiefExperiment uses the basic mechanism, but there is also an advanced (Custom) settings option available.
Where are the reference videos located in the ComfyUI-MotionThiefExperiment examples?
In the ComfyUI-MotionThiefExperiment examples, the reference videos are the first on the left.
How many example videos are provided in the ComfyUI-MotionThiefExperiment documentation?
There are 6 example videos provided in the ComfyUI-MotionThiefExperiment documentation.
What is the purpose of the example videos in the ComfyUI-MotionThiefExperiment documentation?
The example videos in the ComfyUI-MotionThiefExperiment documentation are meant to demonstrate the results of using reference videos for motion in the experimental node pack.
